<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
Males resemble 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. tanintharyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="tanintharyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">M. tanintharyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. but can be distinguished by a thin darkened embolus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Merizocera mainling sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, ventral view C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443248" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">22B</figureCitation>
) (vs. thick and dark only at tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figure 38. Merizocera tanintharyi sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, dorsal view, embolus and conductor distorted C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443264" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">38A</figureCitation>
)), conductor lamina-like and shorter than embolus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Merizocera mainling sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, ventral view C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443248" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">22B</figureCitation>
) (vs. conductor appendage-like and similar length as embolus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figure 38. Merizocera tanintharyi sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, dorsal view, embolus and conductor distorted C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443264" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">38B</figureCitation>
)), presence of clypeus protrusion (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Merizocera mainling sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviations: PT = clypeal protrusion, SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443249" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">23C</figureCitation>
) (vs. absence of clypeal protrusion), absence of cymbial protrusion (vs. presence of cymbial protrusion (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 38" captionStartId="F38" captionText="Figure 38. Merizocera tanintharyi sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, dorsal view, embolus and conductor distorted C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure38" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443264" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">38D</figureCitation>
)). The females can be distinguished by two pairs of twisted spermathecae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Merizocera mainling sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviations: PT = clypeal protrusion, SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443249" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">23A</figureCitation>
) (vs. three pairs of short tubular spermathecae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 39" captionStartId="F39" captionText="Figure 39. Merizocera tanintharyi sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure39" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443266" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">39A</figureCitation>
)).
</paragraph>
